<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-68-0247 </DOCNO><TEXT>A comprehensive survey informs about mining measuring instruments andmethods, monitoring, control and data communication systems, inclusive.Reference is made to several developments which were still in the designor implementation stage. Some of the developments of the past are consideredstate of the art today. The author points out the technical and mentalprocesses changing automation and, what is more, that of undergroundmining, to what it is today. Emphasis is but on some of today's solutions,as there are process computers for control and monitoring purposes, automationof coal extraction, implementation of an open communication system. (orig./MOS)</TEXT></DOC>